ces of philosophy and performance. At times competitive or mutually exclusive, these discourses also merge and engage with each other in creative ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aDramaxTechnique. 0aDrama. 0aTheater and philosophyxTechnique. 0aTheater and philosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Drama.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477588540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804775885423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804775885.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles